# Clarity journey — parked milestones

Read `directions/04-clarity/MILESTONES.md` before editing files in this folder.

## Locked until user explicitly asks otherwise

- **Milestone 1 (Complexity start):** `css/complexity-start.css`, starting-state markup in `journey.html`
- **Milestone 2 (Resting v2):** `css/clarity-rest.css`, resting markup in `journey.html`
- **Milestone 3 (Transitions):** `css/clarity-transition.css`, `css/clarity-layout-lock.css`, `js/clarity-journey.js`

Do not refactor, restyle, or “improve” parked milestones without explicit user approval.

## Minor tweaks only (default)

Threshold nudges, pop timing (`data-pop-at` / `data-pop-delay`), font keyframe values, and copy edits are OK when the user asks. Structural layout changes are not.

## Urgency bar

Parked on `journey.html` (`journey-no-urgency`). See `URGENCY-PARKED.md` to restore.

## Critical regression guards

At `?start=1` with `--u:0`: layout must match Milestone 1 (hero, header, nav, slider).

At `?resting=1` or slider at 100% + rest: must match Milestone 2 v2 / `u=100` geometry (95px headline, 980px width, nav gaps even).

After any edit, verify both URLs before ending the session.

## When user says “park it” / “sign off” / “lock it in”

1. Update `MILESTONES.md` with status and date.
2. Commit if asked.
3. Do not revisit parked CSS unless they explicitly reopen a milestone.

## Common false alarm

Missing widgets or wrong layout often means **resting state** in `localStorage` (`portfolio-clarity-resting`). Use `?start=1`.
